    "The detailed procedure of the MSDD-(IA) 3 is presented in Algorithm 1 and the parameter information is provided in Table 3. for i = 1, 2,..., N si ze do 9: X i = Word_Embedding(X i) + Position_Embedding(X i) 10: for b = 1 to 12 do 11: Q i, K i, V i ← X i 12: X i = Layer N orm(X i + Multi Head b - (I A) 3 (Q i, K i, V i)) 13: X i = Layer N orm(X i + F F N b -(I A) 3 (X i)) Experiment DatasetThe experimental dataset is derived from PyTraceBugs [33] and includes 23,736 defective snippets and 41,012 clean snippets.",
    "The non-defective snippets in this dataset are collected from stable projects in distinct GitHub repositories, while the defective snippets are selected from bug fixes and pull requests in various top repositories.",
    "The Defect types encompass six common types of defects in Python development, as well as other types.",
    "The distribution of types in the defective snippets is presented in Table 4.",
    "Each snippet is labeled according to the following rule: non-defective snippets are marked as 0, defective snippets with six major types of defects are labeled from 1 to 6, and snippets with other defects are marked as 7."
